==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pelton wheel
<hw>Pel"ton wheel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A form of
impulse turbine or water wheel, consisting of a row of double cup-shaped
buckets arranged round the rim of a wheel and actuated by one or more
jets of water playing into the cups at high velocity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peltry</ent>⟦br⟧
